revision.text:
{{Infobox film awards | number = 25 | award = Bangladesh National Film Awards| award_link = National Film Awards (Bangladesh) | image = | alt = | caption = | awarded_for = Best of Bangladeshi cinema in 2000 | award_org = [[President of Bangladesh]] | presenting_org = [[Ministry of Information (Bangladesh)|Ministry of Information]] | announced_date = August 5, 2003 | presented_date = September 10, 2003 | site = Osmany Memorial Hall, [[Dhaka]], [[Bangladesh]] | host = | website = [http://www.moi.gov.bd/ Official website] | best_feature = ''[[Kittonkhola]]'' | best_non_feature = | best_actor = [[Riaz (actor)|Riaz]] | best_actor_film = ''[[Dui Duari]]'' | best_actress = [[Champa (actress)|Champa]] | best_actress_film = ''[[Uttarer Khep]]'' | most_wins = ''[[Kittonkhola]]'' (8) | last = 24th | next = 26th }}
The '''25th Bangladesh National Film Awards''', presented by Ministry of Information, Bangladesh to felicitate the best of Bangladeshi Cinema released in the year 2000. The National Film Awards are the only film awards given by the government itself. Every year, a national panel appointed by the government selects the winning entry, and the award ceremony is held in [[Dhaka]].<ref name=bdnews24>{{cite news|author=Rashed Shaon |date= |title=চার দশকে আমাদের সেরা চলচ্চিত্রগুলো |newspaper=bdnews24 |url=http://glitz.bdnews24.com/details.php?catry=2&showns=2012 |accessdate=November 4, 2012 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130127231625/http://glitz.bdnews24.com/details.php?catry=2&showns=2012 |archivedate=January 27, 2013 |df= }}</ref> The ceremony took place at Osmany Memorial Hall, Dhaka and awards were distributed by former Prime Minister Khaleda Zia. Additionally, Information Minister Tariqul Islam attended the function as the special guest at that evening.<ref name=PM>{{cite news|title=PM to distribute film awards today|url=http://archive.thedailystar.net/2003/09/10/d30910012121.htm|newspaper=The Daily Star|date=2003-09-10|accessdate=October 14, 2015}}</ref>
==List of winners== [[image:Riaz National Award Receiving.jpg|thumb|190px|right|[[Riaz (actor)|Riaz]] taking [[National Film Awards (Bangladesh)|National Film Awards]] from Former Prime Minister Khaleda Zia in 2003]]
A 12-member jury board headed by former secretary A H Mofazzal Karim recommended a total of 16 artists to be awarded for 2000. No awards were given in Best Music Director, and Best Lyrics categories in 2000.
