{{Nihongo|'''''Between the Sky and Sea'''''|ソラとウミのアイダ|Sora to Umi no Aida|lit. "The Space Between the Sky and Sea"}} is a Japanese media franchise owned by ForwardWorks, with [[Oji Hiroi]] credited as the original creator. It primarily consists of a smartphone game, released for [[Android (operating system)|Android]] and [[iOS]] on September 28, 2017. A Microsoft Windows version by [[Hokuto Corporation#DMM|DMM]] will be released in Q2 2018.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://gematsu.com/2017/09/sora-umi-no-aida-smartphones-launches-september-28-japan|title=''Sora to Umi no Aida'' for smartphones launches September 28 in Japan|publisher=Gematsu|date=September 25, 2017|accessdate=December 31, 2017}}</ref> An [[anime]] television series adaptation by [[TMS Entertainment]] premiered on October 4, 2018. [[Sentai Filmworks]] have licensed the series.

==Characters==
;{{Nihongo|Haru Soramachi|空町 春|Soramachi Haru}}
:{{voiced by|[[Karin Takahashi]]}}<ref name="Premiere">{{cite web|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2018-03-26/sora-to-umi-no-aida-anime-staff-cast-october-premiere-revealed/.129540|title=Sora to Umi no Aida Anime's Staff, Cast, October Premiere Revealed|publisher=[[Anime News Network]]|date=March 26, 2018|accessdate=March 26, 2018}}</ref>
:A girl from Tokyo who went to the city of [[Onomichi, Hiroshima|Onomichi]] to pursue her dream of becoming a space fisherman. She is very fond of her grandmother, as well as cute things such as cats.
;{{Nihongo|Namino Murakami|村上 波乃|Murakami Namino}}
:{{voiced by|[[Rika Tachibana]]}}<ref name="Premiere"/>
:A girl from Onomichi who is the most experienced of the group. She initially dislikes Haru due to Haru failing in her first fishing mission. Her favorite food is pancakes.
;{{Nihongo|Ruby Azumi|ルビー・安曇|Rubī Azumi}}
:{{voiced by|[[Honoka Inoue]]}}<ref name="Premiere"/>
:A Japanese-American girl from California who joins the group after saving them when a training session went wrong. She calls herself a "spy" and came to Japan in order to find out about Japan's space fishing technology.
;{{Nihongo|Maiko Sakura|櫻 舞湖|Sakura Maiko}}
:{{voiced by|Momoko Suzuki}}<ref name="Premiere"/>
:A girl from [[Akita Prefecture]] who has a shy personality. It is revealed that she decided to become a space fisherman in order to find information on her older brother, who had disappeared in a fishing expedition years before. She is also initially afraid of water due to an incident during her childhood, but later overcomes this fear.
;{{Nihongo|Makiko Maki|薪 真紀子|Maki Makiko}}
:{{voiced by|Maori Komeno}}<ref name="Premiere"/>
:A girl from [[Kumamoto Prefecture]] who joined the group at the same time as Haru. She is fond of outdoor activities such as cycling. She also used to date older men as a result of her father, who works in the space fishing ministry, frequently being away from home.
;{{Nihongo|Makoto Mitsurugi|美剣 真|Mitsurugi Makoto}}
:{{voiced by|Ai Kōsaka}}<ref name="Premiere"/>
:A girl from Kyoto who is descended from a line of swordmakers. She decided to become a space fisherman despite having a fear of water because she wanted to prove her abilities to her family.

==Media==
===Manga===
A [[manga]] adaptation was serialized by [[ASCII Media Works]] in their ''[[Dengeki Daioh]]'' magazine between September 2017 and November 2018. The series was compiled into two ''[[tankōbon]]'' volumes.<ref>{{cite web |title=Between the Sky and Sea Manga Ends |url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2018-11-25/between-the-sky-and-sea-manga-ends/.139927 |publisher=[[Anime News Network]] |accessdate=December 2, 2018 |date=November 25, 2018}}</ref>

===Anime===
An anime television series adaptation was announced on July 25, 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2017-07-25/forwardworks-sora-to-umi-no-aida-smartphone-game-gets-anime-in-2018/.119292|title=ForwardWorks' ''Sora to Umi no Aida'' Smartphone Game Gets Anime in 2018|publisher=[[Anime News Network]]|date=July 25, 2017|accessdate=December 31, 2017}}</ref> Atsushi Nigorikawa is directing the anime at [[TMS Entertainment]], and Takashi Yamada is in charge of series composition. Shūhei Yamamoto is drawing the character designs.<ref name="Premiere"/> The series premiered on October 4, 2018, on [[Tokyo MX]] and other channels.<ref>{{cite web |title=Sora to Umi no Aida TV Anime's 2nd Promo Video Reveals October 3 Premiere |url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2018-09-10/sora-to-umi-no-aida-tv-anime-2nd-promo-video-reveals-october-3-premiere/.136568 |publisher=[[Anime News Network]] |accessdate=September 10, 2018 |date=September 10, 2018}}</ref>{{efn|Tokyo MX lists the show at 24:00 on October 3, which is at October 4, 2018 at 12:00 a.m.}} The opening theme is {{nihongo|"Sora to Umi no Aida"|ソラとウミのアイダ}} by [[Karin Takahashi]], [[Honoka Inoue]], and Momoko Suzuki under their character names, and the ending theme is {{nihongo|"Ao no Kanata"|蒼の彼方|lit. "Beyond the Blue"}} by [[Konomi Suzuki]].<ref name="October">{{cite web|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2018-08-02/sora-to-umi-no-aida-anime-reveals-theme-song-artists-new-visual/.134976|title=Sora to Umi no Aida Anime Reveals Theme Song Artists, New Visual|publisher=Anime News Network|date=August 2, 2018|accessdate=August 9, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/soraumi_app/status/1024862370206642176|title=ソラウミアニメ オープニングテーマはこの曲|last=|first=|date=August 1, 2018|website=|publisher=[[Twitter]]|language=Japanese|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=August 2, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=ソラウミアニメ エンディング曲決定！ |url=https://twitter.com/soraumi_app/status/1024638585847263232 |publisher=[[Twitter]] |accessdate=August 1, 2018 |language=Japanese |date=August 1, 2018}}</ref> The series will run for 12 episodes.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/daily-briefs/2018-10-01/sora-to-umi-no-aida-anime-listed-with-12-episodes/.137511|title=Sora to Umi no Aida Anime Listed With 12 Episodes|publisher=[[Anime News Network]]|date=October 1, 2018|accessdate=October 1, 2018}}</ref> [[Crunchyroll]] is streaming the series,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2018-10-02/crunchyroll-streams-between-the-sky-and-sea-run-with-the-wind/.137587|title=Crunchyroll Streams Between the Sky and Sea, Run with the Wind|publisher=[[Anime News Network]]|date=October 2, 2018}}</ref> while Sentai Filmworks have licensed the series.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2018-11-14/sentai-filmworks-licenses-between-the-sky-and-sea-anime/.139477|title=Sentai Filmworks Licenses Between the Sky and Sea Anime|publisher=Anime News Network|date=November 14, 2018|accessdate=November 14, 2018}}</ref>

