{{Infobox video game |title = Cities XL 2012 |image = Cities XL 2012 cover.jpg |caption = |developer = [[Focus Home Interactive]] |publisher = Focus Home Interactive |series = ''[[Cities XL]]'' |released = October 20, 2011<ref name="releasedate">[http://eu-focushop.gamesplanet.com/shop/citiesxl2012] Cities Xl 2012, Release Date {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111012155126/http://eu-focushop.gamesplanet.com/shop/citiesxl2012 |date=October 12, 2011 }}</ref> |genre = [[City simulator]] |modes = [[Single-player]] |platforms = [[Microsoft Windows]] }} '''''Cities XL 2012''''' is a [[city simulator]] developed by [[Focus Home Interactive]]. ''Cities XL 2012'' is the third game in the ''[[Cities XL]]'' franchise. The game focuses on a [[single-player video game|single-player mode]], and was released on October 20, 2011.<ref name="releasedate"/> New features include new structures, new maps and a starter guide; additionally, the game has been opened to [[Mod (video gaming)|modding]] and allows players to share their mods. It is fully compatible with ''Cities XL 2011'' version with a discounted upgrade available.<ref name=CitiesXL2012pr>{{cite web|title=Cities XL 2012 unveiled with images!|url=http://www2.citiesxl.com/index.php?rub=news-info&id=74|work=Cities XL Official Website|accessdate=11 October 2011|date=13 July 2011}}</ref> An [[expansion pack]] was released simultaneously.<ref name=CitiesXLdownload>{{cite web|title=Cities XL Download Center|url=http://www2.citiesxl.com/index.php?rub=downloads|work=Cities XL Official Website|accessdate=11 October 2011}}</ref>
==Development== The game was officially announced by Focus Home Interactive on July 13, 2011.<ref name=CitiesXL2012pr/> Cities XL first released on October 8–9, 2009, with the following Cities XL 2011 released on October 14, 2010, then Cities XL 2012 on October 20, 2011. The game was developed by Focus Home Interactive and originally published by [[Monte Cristo (company)|Monte Cristo]].
== Reception == Cities XL 2012 received mixed reviews from various critics. It currently has a rating of 61/100 on [[Metacritic]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.metacritic.com/game/pc/cities-xl-2012 |title=Cities XL 2012 for PC Reviews, Ratings, Credits, and More |publisher=Metacritic |date= |accessdate=2013-02-05}}</ref>
The biggest weakness of the game is the single core support from the old gaming engine and the poor memory management that slowed the game down in large cities.{{Citation needed|date=June 2013}} The fan base has demanded a recompilation of the source code for years.{{Citation needed|date=June 2013}}
