{{About||the character from ''[[Lilo and Stitch]]''|Cobra Bubbles|the [[BioShock]] character|Big Daddy (BioShock)}}
{{Distinguish|Mr. Bubble}}
{{Refimprove|date=September 2010}}

'''Mr. Bubbles''' is one of several [[brand name]]s that have been used by an entity variously known as Chemtoy, Tootsietoy, and StromBecKer for its [[soap bubble|bubble]]-blowing solution. The company is currently owned by J. Lloyd International and markets under [[TootsieToy]]. J. Lloyd International also owns the rights to the name StromBecKer. It still contains a traditional "[[magic wand]]."

The formula of Mr. Bubbles is proprietary and is among those preferred by bubble trick performers such as [[Sterling Johnson (performer)|Sterling Johnson]] to make up part or all of the mixtures they use. It is also used by [[Cirque du Soleil]].<ref>http://www.mrbubbles.com/history.html  {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080530192523/http://www.mrbubbles.com/history.html |date=May 30, 2008 }}</ref>

Mr. Bubbles celebrated its 75th year of operation in 2008 with the release of several new products,<ref>http://www.mrbubbles.com/bubblefigures.html#1210  {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080618002229/http://www.mrbubbles.com/bubblefigures.html#1210 |date=June 18, 2008 }}</ref> such as a classic Mr. Bubbles Figure Bank, which converts to a [[bank]] when the solution is gone.

