{{Underlinked|date=October 2017}}
{{Orphan|date=October 2017}}
}}

A '''tip jar''' is a game similar to a [[raffle]]. Players buy folded or sealed pieces of paper dealt from large glass jars in hopes of winning prizes. The pieces of paper conceal numbers or symbols that may entitle the purchaser to winnings immediately after opening the ticket. Tip jars were named at a time when the betting slips were tipped out of bags into glass jars or fish bowls. Jars are not necessarily needed. The tickets can be spread out in a pile or pinned on a board.<ref>{{cite web|title=Class II Games: Punch Boards, Tip Jars, and Instant Bingo|url=http://www.nigc.gov/Reading_Room/Bulletins/Bulletin_No._1999-2.aspx|publisher=National Indian Gaming Commission|work=nigc.gov|accessdate=7 April 2012}}</ref>

==References==
{{Reflist}}

[[Category:Gambling games]]

'''''The Arena Spectacular''''' is a live adaptation of the award-winning television series ''[[Walking with Dinosaurs]]''. Like the TV series, ''The Arena Spectacular'' has to recreate [[dinosaurs]] to the point of the viewers accepting the creatures as real.
==Production== [[File:Walking with Dinosaurs.jpg|thumb|Tyrannosaurs in the arena]] ''The Arena Spectacular'' was created by [[The Creature Technology Company]].<ref name=":1">{{Cite news|url=http://www.heraldsun.com.au/entertainment/arts/walking-with-dinosaurs-brings-245-million-years-of-history-to-stage/news-story/6d43a37d1ae60d9cba95e74c0c9e390e?nk=40c2e0e55993d70807ba3c22467f1ab3-1515737865|title=245 million years of history on stage|access-date=2018-01-12|language=en}}</ref> The production cost $20 million to stage, and 20 dinosaurs representing 10 species were created for the show, using [[puppetry]], [[Dinosaur suit|suits]], and [[animatronics]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://fox6now.com/2014/10/15/stepping-into-the-world-of-dinosaurs-sneak-peek-of-walking-with-dinosaurs-arena-spectacular/|title="Stepping into the world of dinosaurs:" Sneak peek of "Walking with Dinosaurs" arena spectacular!|date=2014-10-15|work=FOX6Now.com|access-date=2018-01-12|language=en-US}}</ref> Each large dinosaur weighs several tons, and is operated by two "voodoo puppeteers" and a driver beneath the dinosaur who also monitors the hydraulics and batteries.<ref name=":0">{{Cite news|url=http://www.bbcamerica.com/anglophenia/2014/09/unusually-historical-theater-show-walking-dinosaurs|title=Behind-the-Scenes of ‘Walking with Dinosaurs’ {{!}} BBC America|work=BBC America|access-date=2018-01-12|language=en-US}}</ref> The smaller dinosaurs (marked by an *) are suits operated by the person in it, each weighing from 20–30&nbsp;kg (44-66&nbsp;lbs).<ref name=":0" /> There are six puppeteers for these suits, which only have side views.<ref name=":1" /> The dinosaurs featured are:
*''[[Allosaurus]]'' *''[[Ankylosaurus]]'' *''[[Brachiosaurus]]'' (adolescent) *''[[Brachiosaurus]]'' (adult) *''[[Iguanodon]]'' (carcass) *''[[Liliensternus]]''* *''[[Ornithocheirus]]'' *''[[Plateosaurus]]'' (adult) *''[[Plateosaurus]]'' (2 hatchlings) *''[[Stegosaurus]]'' *''[[Torosaurus]]'' (2x) *''[[Tyrannosaurus]]'' (adult) *''[[Tyrannosaurus]]'' (juvenile)* *''[[Utahraptor]]'' (3x)* The dinosaurs initially did not have feathers, but they were later added after new research showed dinosaurs possessed plumage.<ref name=":1" /> This also necessitated rewrites of the script, which were added to later iterations of the show as well as improvements in the animatronics, making them more responsive to puppeteers and giving them the ability to "eat" food and spray water vapor as "breath".<ref name=":1" />
==Tours== ''The Arena Spectacular'' originated in [[Australia]] in January 2007 (as ''Walking with Dinosaurs: The Live Experience''), and toured [[North America]] in 2007–10, [[Europe]] in 2010, and returned to North America until 2011. It also toured [[Asia]] beginning in December 2010. In 2011 the show came to its final destination of its first tour, [[New Zealand]]. In 2012, the show toured the UK, Germany, Ireland, Norway, Sweden, Denmark, Finland, and the Netherlands.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-1085030/T-rex-comes-town-Stunning-10m-life-size-dinosaurs-stomps-Britain.html|title=T-rex comes to town: Stunning £10m show with life-size dinosaurs stomps towards Britain|work=Mail Online|access-date=2018-01-12}}</ref> For 2018, the show will be touring only the UK from Summer until Christmas 2018.
